List up to ten (10) things you want to say to ten (10) different people. Do not state who these people are. Do not confirm or deny any 'comment speculation.' Tag five (5) people.

1. Sometimes I still think you are the one
2. I never imagined having my wedding and you not being there
3. Sometimes I wish I could see you just one more time even though I hate your guts just so I could rub it in your face that your life will never be as good as mine because you are a loser, always have been and always will be.
4. I still think about you almost everyday, and everytime I think about you I cry
5. Butt out and leave us alone
6. I think you are the reason for all of the problems he is having right now
7. You can get better but I dont think you want to
8. I'm glad we got back in touch
9. you absolutely suck at keeping in touch, ever since college really, but when you do get in touch it is great
10. what happened never should have happened. I wish I could erase it all from memory

The whole time we were on holiday the boy seemed fine. I thought his medicine was really working for him. Since we have been home he has seemed out of it and down. Told me the medicine doesn't really work anymore. He has been having weird things going on. Said his finger was burning the other day then yesterday it hurt. Last night while sleeping he was holding my arm and his fingers were moving a mile a minute even though he wasn't doing it. Now this morning he is complaining that all his joints are still and hurt. I wonder if it is only this place that fucks up his brain.

Waiting for him to get out of the shower so we can go out. I need to buy computer paper. I have a paper due on Friday, I went to print it out last night and would you believe it I ran out of paper! I am nervous about the assignments I have to hand in. Brittish grading is different you can get a pass merit or distinction. They give you a guide about what entails which but I cant write an assignment while looking at guides like that. I need to just let it flow or it feels like pulling teeth.
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/11768.html

Went to the pub for dinner tonight, we need to go food shopping and had no food that we wanted to eat so we went out. There was a new guy working there. I went up to order and he was flirting with me. It was nice to have someone hit on me even though I am attached. Made me smile.
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/11513.html

I am grumpy lately. I am taking it out on Edward without meaning it. Little things he does are annoying the hell out of me. Like he constantly picks food off my plate. Thats my food damn it. And this morning when I wanted to come on the computer to do my homework he actually told me to do it while he was at work later cause it was more productive. Why? So he could play a video game! I was fuming and he doesn't understand why.
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/11252.html

Ok, so it is a bit of an exaturation since no one in the woodrow wilson knows us by name but god it felt good to be back in our local pub. I think that is what I missed most while on holiday. Not that I am an alchie it is just very cozy and a weekly (if not daily) stop for Edward and I. I really wish they would stock Jack Daniels though. But then again what is the point when your in the UK supplying American wiskey when Scotland is only a few miles away and that is the home of Wiskey. Whatever it was nice.

We have only been back 28 hours and Josie is already calling. God I hate that woman. Can we have a chance to breath before you start demanding Edward's time? 

I bought 2 rolls of Winnie the Pooh wrapping paper for half price today:) Along with some tubs to put he Christmas and Halloween decorations away in, Shampoo, Conditioner and Ibpreufon.
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/10856.html

There is something big and I feel the need to get it off my chest. I have thought of writting it here a few times but then I wonder if it would not be better to just write it in a letter. I am driving myself a little crazy thinking about it.

The past few days I have not been sleeping well. The silence, the time when you are completely alone and have to face your fears and dreams when your lying in bed inbetween sleep and awake has been driving me insane. Why cant my brain just have a shut off valve?

Edward has been spending the past few days sleeping in very late. Like right now it is 2 in the afternoon. Tomorrow we need to be at the train by quarter past 8 in the morning. He better be prepared to wake up and I dont give a fuck how tired he is. I want to go home!
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/10700.html

We went out for Italian tonight in Aberdeen. It was absolute shit. I didn't enjoy it nad it was way too expensive. I feel really bad but I am still hungry and want to make food but I dont want to offend Edwards mom who paid.
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/10478.html

So I didn't get to leave the cottage at all yesterday! But in a good note there were a few times when Edward and I were utterly alone and it was nice. He built a fire and we just hung out. We want a house like this one day.

I watched a program on Torrets. It was so interesting. The more I see these types of things the more I think I am destined to teach children with special needs. I guess we will find out.

I hate to say it but I really dont like his younger sister Jackie. I have only just met her recently even though I knew everyone else. She just seems bitchy. He even said she is acting really bad towards his mother. Last night his mother was taking her nad her friend out and while her mother wasn't looking she stole the car keys and was driving the car around the backyard. I know it is not horrible but she is old enough to know it is wrong. And Edward has told me she has wrecked a few of the families cars by fucking around in them. Cars are not toys.

Today we are supposed to be going out but it is only going ot be for like 2 hours. I WANT TO GO HOME. I want to be able to go out whenever I please. I dont want to have to wait for other people to decide they are ready.

I got an email today about room changes for one of my upcoming modules. It starts a week later then it was supposed to. Thats nice I guess. I am ready to go back though.
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/10129.html

Last night Edward and Stuart stayed up til 3 am playing Halo 2. Not wanting to look the wimp I stayed up with them even though at 11 I was struggling to keep my eyes open. This morning I woke up to screams through out the house. Some kind of drama so I stayed in bed not wanting to walk into the middle of a battlefield. When I did wake up Stuart told me I had to wake Edward up cause it was 11am and late. Granted it is later then we normally wake up but we were up to fucking 3 am for fucks sake. And it is his fault we were up that long to begin with! I wanted to tell him off but he is harmless so I refrained myself. The littlest things really tick me off lately. I dont know why. Not like my period is coming or anything.

I just keep thinking how I want to be home. I have homework to do and cant get myself to do it here. And this house is like 12 miles out of town so unless Edward's mom drives us we cant go anywhere. I get cabin fever very easily. I am like a dog. I need to go out like once a day or I start to freak out. I dont like that someone else is in control of when I can and cant go out or come home.

I am like a freak when I am on vacation. I feel like if it something I can do at home like watch tv then it isn't worth doing on vacation but we dont seem to be doing much in the way of anything. Bleh.
http://feelin-bothered.livejournal.com/9880.html

right so I may have broken down and come back to blogging. we shall see if it lasts. Maybe it is only because I am sitting here at quarter to midnight while Stuart and Edward are playing xbox and I am bored? Maybe I actually have some shit to say. 

I dont know if anyone will read this...most likely not but whatever. So I am lame, I dont know how to make pretty layouts on livejournal since I just never bothered to learn while making all my layouts for kiwi which I dont use anymore. So you will have to bare with me and my boring layout.

Just a few minutes ago I had to first IM from someone on AIM that I dont know in ages. Of course I didn't accept the IM because I believe if it was anyone important I would already know them, but then you always wonder who it was and why they were IMing you. Hoping it wasn't some stupid perv sending porn.

I feel like I have something to say but I am sitting here with a lack of words flowing from my fingers.

Have been spending a few days with Edwards family. I always feel a little out of place around them. I am not really enjoying myself. I dont want to be a baby but they keep this house so fucking cold. For the past few days I have been wearing my coat in the house. That just doesn't fly with me. When in the house I like to wear the least amount of clothes as possible. Edward keeps asking why I dont tell anyone but the cold doesn't seem to bother anyone else so I dont want to be the nagging one. But if I get fucking Pnemonia they will be sorry.

Today Edward and I had planned to go shopping but then we stopped by Stuarts house and he came out with us. Even though we walked into stores I couldn't really shop because they were following me kind of sulking. Then they freaked out when Edward's mom asked if I bought anything and I said no and told her why. She said the girls would go shopping another day. That sounds nice and I guess I should bond with my future mother nad sisters in law but it is a scary thought as well.

One and Edward's sisters has 5 kids, one of them spend the weekend and I was told when he went back to his dads today he was talking about his Auntie Mary. That is so strange having someone call me Auntie. I have gone from having no siblings to having 4 sister in laws and 3 nieces and 2 nephews. I just cant get my mind around it sometimes.

Your Inner European is Irish!
Sprited and boisterous! You drink everyone under the table.
Who's Your Inner European?

I love Edward. I want to be supportive but sometimes I just dont feel like it is fair. Whenever I get really down about being apart and talk to him about it he gets really down and then I have to be the one that has it together. Why? What if I want to break down? What if I need someone to hold it together for me? He says everything seems pointless so he winds up not going to school or to work. Well I really know what pointless is. When I wake up everyday with nothing to do. I hate having to try and convince him to go to school. Why cant he just deal with it by himself? I feel horrible writting this but everyone needs to rant about the one they love sometimes right?

So I called Edward this morning to make sure he was up for school. I had my doubts that he would acutally go so then when he was supposed to be in school I called the house and he didn't answer so I thought Great! He went to school. Then I called again when he should have been in work and he didn't answer so I thought Great! He went to work. But now I want him home. I want to talk to him make sure he is ok and that I wasn't too hard on him. What is wrong with me. Then I get to thinking maybe he just isn't answering the phone so that I dont know he didn't go. What a freak.

And why the hell is my entry from last night posted under Wenesday?
